</code><code>
</code><code>
</code></td></tr><tr><td class="number">8</td><td class="junk"></td><td class="xsl" ><code>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</code><code>Sec. 1. </code><code>
</code><code>Unless the context otherwise requires, the words </code></td></tr><tr><td class="number">9</td><td class="junk"></td><td class="xsl" ><code>defined in this
Section have the following meanings as used in </code></td></tr><tr><td class="number">10</td><td class="junk"></td><td class="xsl" ><code>this Act.</code><code>
</code></td></tr><tr><td class="number">11</td><td class="junk"></td><td class="xsl" ><code>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</code><code>"Person" means any natural person, corporation, </code></td></tr><tr><td class="number">12</td><td class="junk"></td><td class="xsl" ><code>association,
partnership, governmental agency or other legal </code></td></tr><tr><td class="number">13</td><td class="junk"></td><td class="xsl" ><code>entity, receiver, trustee,
guardian, executor, administrator, </code></td></tr><tr><td class="number">14</td><td class="junk"></td><td class="xsl" ><code>fiduciary or representative of any kind.</code><code>
</code></td></tr><tr><td class="number">15</td><td class="junk"></td><td class="xsl" ><code>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</code><code>"Oil" means natural crude oil or petroleum and other </code></td></tr><tr><td class="number">16</td><td class="junk"></td><td class="xsl" ><code>hydrocarbons,
regardless of gravity, which are produced at the </code></td></tr><tr><td class="number">17</td><td class="junk"></td><td class="xsl" ><code>well in liquid form by
ordinary production methods or by the </code></td></tr><tr><td class="number">18</td><td class="junk"></td><td class="xsl" ><code>use of an oil and gas separator and
